location.fullValue: Coral II Plan, Banning Lewis Ranch

data.description:
Situated in the Indigo Ranch community, this expansive two-story home boasts stunning mountain views, offers three bedrooms and three bathrooms and features a host of impressive upgrades including a brand-new roof, newly stained deck, new interior paint, new carpet, and newly refinished hardwood floors. Additional enhancements include new smoke and carbon monoxide detectors, newer water heater, stainless steel kitchen appliances, and a farmhouse kitchen sink. 

The home is adorned with upgraded light fixtures, faucets, hardware, and doorknobs throughout, providing a polished and cohesive aesthetic. A whole-house fan, front storm door, two-sided gas fireplace, two-panel doors, and ceiling fans add to the comfort and functionality. The property also includes an unfinished basement, offering full potential for customization, as well as an ADT security system for peace of mind. Outside, the fully fenced backyard is complemented by an expansive deck and storage shed, while the garage boasts an epoxied floor and custom shelving. 

Upon entering the front door, you'll immediately appreciate the open, airy, light, and bright ambiance, as well as the distinctive architectural details. The main level seamlessly connects the living and dining areas, a welcoming kitchen, a powder bathroom, access to the garage/laundry area, and backyard. Ascend to the upper level to discover the spacious primary suite (offering room for a sitting area, desk/work zone, or workout space), along with an upgraded five-piece ensuite and a cedar-lined walk-in closet.

Two additional bedrooms (each offering mountain views), and a full bathroom complete the upper level. Descend downstairs to the unfinished basement, which comes equipped with rough-in plumbing and provides plenty of room for storage. Conveniently located near parks, recreational centers, trails, military bases, shopping, dining, entertainment, businesses, schools, and the like, schedule a showing before it's too late!
